I hope that by 2016 the whole Old Kazan Street will be restored, - says the official.
The houses will have a proper look, corresponding to what they were before, three centuries ago.
Demidov's house is likely to become a museum open to all.
In addition, the government has decided to make the street pedestrian on weekends.
Unfortunately, we can't do it on weekdays, because the city's too busy.
Vladimir Barabash promises to move people from the future museum in 2015.
However, they are unlikely to be satisfied: their new apartments will be the same size as the current ones.
Just from another era.
